<time>1519959473865<//time><Rate>1</Rate>< review>
The surgeon here named Eric Crum is the worst. Avoid him at all costs. He pulled all of my wisdom teeth on Friday February 16, 2018. I felt the bottom one, and he knew I felt it, and did not give me anymore numbing medication. He proceeded to pull the tooth out, until it was completely out. It literally felt like I was being shocked,/electrocuted. There was massive pain, due to the fact that the roots were being pulled out with the tooth. The pain I felt is indescribable. It was a very traumatic and painful experience. My boyfriend was waiting for me when I came out of the office. When we stepped out of the office I started crying immediately . I told my boyfriend about what I had just gone through and how I was treated. He was beyond upset. If I could I would give him negative stars. He should not do what he does. He has absolutely no compassion for others. And two spots in my mouth where I had lost teeth previously had slivers of teeth still in there. He cleaned those all out and removed the rementants of the teeth, so I thought. I pulled a piece of tooth out today with tweezers that he didn't, because it was stabbing me in the tounge. I decided to add some pictures. Thank you and the best of luck to you.

So I just thought I would post an update. I went out of town on vacation and ended up going to an Urgent Care in La Quinta, CA., due to severe pain from my dental procedure. I was prescribed a strong antibiotic and pain medication. We I returned home, I had a letter from the dental group waiting for me. I believe I was sent this letter due to the review I left. Good luck to all of those who choose this place.<//review>

< Text>
I used to have a dentist for more than 15 years in Fair Oaks. I was forced to move on due to the insurance practices. I found Redford's office through Delta website. And they accepted both of my insurance. I did my research before I tried to make an appointment. I have had pretty bad experience with dentists who accepted Delta HMO. I read all of reviews online and attempted to see the appearance of the offices and what kind of patients they had. So I tried it. I accepted what I saw at my first appointment which was cleaning. This is the only office that started with cleaning appointment first. I was kind of happy with that because that was what I wanted to see how it is.

Then they referred me to another office for root canals. I had doubt on even when I had experience with this kind of setup before. However, this is the only office that pointed out to the internal infection.

At the root canal place, it was busy. Everyone was busy in there. But the dentist who performed the root canals seem to very very proficient. My long time dentist did everything himself. Root canal took him a lot longer than this one. I was extremely happy with his work.

Thank you all for the job well done.< /Text>

I started to get a bubble like form. I understand that being fitted into the schedule and being assign to a HIGH list of HMO patients there is going to be a wait. You just have to make sure you actually have a doctor that care for you. The staff has always been great to me. At first I thought that they were not trying to help me and after my their visit I realize how friendly and helping they are. It's hard to understand how the Community Manager I work with at my property (not to mention his VP) manages to keep a job. These guys almost never respond to emails and phone calls. In the rare instances when they do respond, it's just an obligatory response but it never leads to substantive feedback or resolution of issues. I've had times where I've followed up three, four, five times and there's no response. I pay my $400 bill to First Service on the first of every month... always on time, never late... yet the people with the words "community manager" in their titles don't bother to respond to members of the community. This is in a time where many of the amenities I'm paying for haven't been accessible for the last year (pool, jacuzzi, sauna, gym). Quite the business model this company has going for itself. This place has an average rating of 2.3 as of this message, which is awful (and predictable), but it's shocking to me that it's that high.

[UPDATE: After speaking with Terri a couple of times, I am optimistic that my concerns have been heard and positive change is coming. Based on that, I'm changing my rating from 1 star to 3 stars based on the professionalism, understanding, and commitment to improvement showed by Terri in dealing with my concerns.]<//Text>

<name>David Parikh< /name>< review>
JUST PAY YOU CANNOT WIN.

I paid my association dues, but the amount was credited to the wrong account.  I called in to verify on the 15th of this month. I was told that the money was transferred to the correct account, but it looks like it was transferred after the 15ht. So I got a late fee per their statement.

Just got off the phone with First Service Customer Care in Florida.  She said that I shouldn't have to pay the late fee, but she would put in a request with the board.  But if I pay only this month's dues, I will owe the amount of the late fee on the 15th if the request to wave the late fees is not approved and processed before the 15th.

So I will owe late fees on the late fees, additionally they now charge a new Processing fee.  I guess this money goes to FSR and not the association.  Just noticed it on the bill:
"Please note should your account become more than 60 days past due a $75.00 processing fee will be charged." (Noted)

My Suggestions for those of us who purchased a home managed by FSR:

* Always pay by paper check, and write your address on the memo line.  That way you have proof.
*Call in to check on the status of your account.  If they make a mistake, or you don't know about the charges you are still responsible.  I would suggest you pay on the first and call in around the 8th of the month so you can mail them another check before the 15th.</review>

< Review>
Tight and noisy, this place is hell for hamsters and birds, their cages are too small and overcrowded with the animals looking sickly and halfway dead. The only good thing here is the fish cages which is actually what they seem to care about. The fish tank water is always clean with no dead fishes floating around, and all seem to be bright and happy. Don't bother buying supplies here because you'll be ripped off. Only semi good note is that they will buy any hamsters from you if your hamsters accidentally bred or you got two different genders accidentally. I think they also do the same with birds.<//Review>

<userid>107172186840901680823</userid><Response>None< /Response><time>1465233482255<//time>< Text>
Found this LFS by chance on Craigslist. Ad mention a large variety of hard to find pleco's so I decided to make the 20 mile drive to check it out. My first impression was that this place is small and I won't find what I'm looking for. Well I guessed wrong. Found an EDJD for 12.99. 12.99!!! My LFS wanted between $20-$40 for a 1" and got me a close to 2" for a lot leas. Also their pleco selection didn't disappoint. Vampires, golden nuggets, royals, avocado, and pelckoltia compta. Picked up a 2" pelckoltia for $12.99 which I found to be a bargain. Definitely will make the 20 mile drive in the future when I get a larger tank.< /Text>

<review>It was saturday night. After passing this location looking for a good desert and meeting disappointment, I decided that shaved ice was a good idea. I spent a minutes looking over the menu, which is very well put together, might I add. There were several very satisfied customers out front on the tables so I was sure this was a good pick.  I started to order and was interrupted with "sorry, hold on 1 second" while she walked to the back talking with someone and comes back. She said "I'm sorry we are closed and can't serve you." I looked at my watch its 11:01 they close at 11:00. Might I add that we had traveled out of our way to find a place that was open this late. I will not be returning to this location unless it is the only place in a zombie apocalypse with the cure to save the world. I hope the owner finds a way to handle situations like this in the future.< /review><pics>None</pics><Resp>None< /Resp>< gmap_id>
0x80c2bb0ac534e4c9:0x475b10ab6a9be664</gmap_id>
</record></dataset><record>
<UserId.>110006480612793104456< /UserId.><user_name>Steven Vong< /user_name><Date>1453529624722</Date><Rate>4<//Rate>< Review>
Brian's shaved Ice is almost as good as the product in Hawaii- still a solid choice for dessert in Sawtelle. You can choose 2/3 syrup flavors to add to your ice cone and even add dole whip or ice cream in the middle! The small is actually a good portion and sometimes even sharable amongst two if you just want a small bite.

The ice here is pretty fine with a few coarse bits. They have a huge amount of flavors to choose from and give a good amount of syrup- I'm sure you can also ask for extra. The condensed milk is always a delicious addition and they don't skimp. The dole whip is refreshing and I like the vanilla ice cream too. This is as close to Hawaiian shaved ice as you can get in West LA!< /Review>

< text>
Best Hawaiian shaved ice I've ever had! When I first went there, I was like "how good can shaved ice be, it's just crushed ice cubes" and was delightfully proven wrong. They get their ice shavers from Hawaii, so it is true to its name and oh so delicious. The shave ice is really soft and flavorful. Make sure to get dole whip inside your shaved ice (or just separately) to round out your Hawaiian experience!!

Sometimes when I'm not feelin shaved ice, I just go there for their dole whip or ice cream. They have yummy ice cream flavors, like white chocolate macadamia or green tea (my personal favorite).

Definitely stop by at least once when you're in Sawtelle and you want an alternative to the never ending boba or blockheads!<//text>
